      "content": "Oh, my bad, I thought you had the PDF uploaded to your system. Here is the text from Section 4.2: \n\n\"4.2 Price Adjustments: During peak demand months (defined as June-August), the Supplier reserves the right to implement a price increase of up to 5% over the previous month's rate to account for market volatility. Such adjustments shall be communicated via email to the Client 7 days prior to the effective date.\"\n\nSo, looking at that, does this give them the right to change our rates unexpectedly without us needing to negotiate or agree to it in writing first? We really need to avoid these kinds of unilateral hikes.",
